<br>
What I would like to see is an increase in the amount of damage done by mana burn.  Right now it's really inefficient.  It's great for one big blast to put a dent in a mob's hp, or to instantly destroy Gore (*wink*), but without some way to regain that mana, it's going to be like Harvest.  I'll reserve it for an emergency situation.  Strike of Solusek is going to do 2700 points of damage, and it may be resistable, but I'll be able to cast it many times in a single battle.  Add to that focus effects, and the AA fury abilities and I may be able to pull 6k out of a single nuke, if I get the right numbers.  That's pretty close to a non-crit manaburn at a fraction of the cost.<br>
<br>
I would also like to see the reuse timer set back to 72 minutes.  Right now it's at 2 hours, 24 minutes.  Hell, maybe even 60 would be nice.<br>
<br>
One thing I'd really want to see is an increase in the efficiency of our standard nukes.  We're not that much more efficient than mages, and we don't have pets to back us up or tank for us.<br>
<br>
It's the T-rod issue I'm really worried about now.  I don't know.  Dalnin?  What do you think? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bcircleofsisters.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalnin>Dalnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder<br>Paddle Mistress</span><br>  Posts: 527<br> <font color=#660000>(10/10/02 12:22:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=744.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: *Cries*</span><hr size=1> T rods are the real change to the game. basically you can generate infinite mana with them they way they are so like al things that do that they will go away<br>
